FuncDef: This command displays memory allocation failure rate of the specified ISA. The system collects usage information every hour for last 24 hours. The output also includes a current value.

ParaDef.Info: Displays information about the specified ISA. Values-slot/mda.
Displays information for the number of statistics intervals to be displayed (starting with the most recent). Values-1 to 24.
Displays information about the specified period covered by the statistics to be displayed (starting with the most recent). Values-1 to 1440.
Displays information about the current statistic value. The values of count and minutes are ignored by the system once this parameter is specified.
Displays information about the Object Identifier (OID) of the current statistical value.
